on and solutions. The text is accompanied by lively case studies of both success and failure in virtual learning environments. Inspiring stories of student learning illustrate the power of MUVE to transform health care education. This innovative handbook presents an extended discussion of the pedagogical advantages for learning in multi-user virtual environments, along with a history of learning in Second Life®. The text includes an appendix of supporting materials for MUVE learning activities: evaluation grids, grading matrices, syllabus descriptions, and detailed orientation materials for both faculty and students. While the sample learning activities were designed for nurses, instructors in other disciplines could easily adapt them for use in any MUVE setting.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aNursingxStudy and teachingxSimulation methods. 0aShared virtual environments. 7aMEDICAL / Health Care Delivery.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311056413640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780824858032zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824858032zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824858032/original  a978-3-11-056413-6 UHP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA